snippet.textDisplay: The good news is that after having watched something like two dozen clips, I'm not tired of seeing XIAOMA and Company interacting with Chinese people, who are indeed appreciative that foreigners have invested this much time and effort into learning not one, but THREE Chinese dialects.  The bad news? It's going to be harder and harder to surprise people as they become more and more well-known. I've seen both young and old people in Chinatown recognizing them, which maybe is why Xiaoma decided to try his hand at Korean? I can't wait to see what happens once he's been going at that for a year!

The bad news? It's going to be harder and harder to surprise people as they become more and more well-known. I've seen both young and old people in Chinatown recognizing them, which maybe is why Xiaoma decided to try his hand at Korean? I can't wait to see what happens once he's been going at that for a year!
